  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nConceptually the `p2p` module is intended to be *pure* DevP2P library code, and the `trinity` module should be all of the components built on top of the `p2p` module which are used to construct our ethereum node.\r\n\r\nCurrently, much of the Trinity code is living in the `p2p` module.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nGet all of the following moved to live under the `trinity` module.\r\n\r\n- everything in `p2p.eth`\r\n- everything in `p2p.les`\r\n- everything in `p2p.lightchain`\r\n- `p2p.peer`\r\n  - minor refactor to `p2p.peer.BasePeer` to relocate `genesis` and `_local_chain_info`.\r\n  - `p2p.peer..LESPeer`\r\n  - `p2p.peer..EthPeer`\r\n  - `p2p.peer..PeerPoolSubscriber`\r\n  - `p2p.peer..PeerPool`\r\n- everything in `p2p.rlp` ( \r\n- everything in `p2p.sedes`\r\n- everything in `p2p.server`\r\n- everything in `p2p.sharding_peer` and `p2p.sharding_protocol`, `p2p.shard_syncer`\r\n- everything in `p2p.state`\r\n- everything in `p2p.sync`\r\n- `p2p.utils`\r\n  - `p2p.utils.sequence_builder`",
